# Accessibility

## Elements
- `<button>` for actions, `<a>`/`<Link>` for navigation — never `<div>` with onClick
- Icon-only buttons need `aria-label`
- Decorative images: `alt=""` and `aria-hidden="true"`
- Meaningful images: descriptive `alt` text (describe information, not the image)
- Semantic HTML (`<nav>`, `<main>`, `<section>`, `<header>`) before ARIA roles
- Hierarchical headings h1-h6; include skip link for main content

## Forms
- Every input needs a visible `<label>` (placeholders are not labels)
- Correct `type` attribute: email, tel, url, number
- `autocomplete` attribute on relevant fields
- Never block paste on inputs
- Errors inline next to fields with `aria-describedby`; focus first error on submit
- Labels clickable via `htmlFor` or wrapping

## Focus
- Visible focus ring: `focus-visible` with 2-3px outline, 3:1 contrast minimum
- Never `outline: none` without `:focus-visible` replacement
- Interactive states increase contrast: hover/active/focus more prominent than rest

## Motion & Media
- `prefers-reduced-motion`: provide crossfade or disable spatial motion
- Images need explicit `width` and `height` to prevent CLS
- Below-fold images: `loading="lazy"`

## Touch
- Minimum 44x44px touch targets (use padding or pseudo-elements if visual size is smaller)
- `touch-action: manipulation` to prevent double-tap zoom delay

## Content
- Active voice for instructions
- Specific button labels: "Save API Key" not "Continue"
- Error messages include the fix, not just the problem
